Notes:
dataptr is a pointer.  Data pointer.  unsigned char is a byte string

int* declares a pointer
&david retrieves the memory adress of david
david* retrieves the data at the memory adress david

cBuffer david;
(cBuffer*)&david casts the pointer &david to be a pointer to cBuffer

unsigned char data[50] ; allocates memory 50 contiguous unsigned characters, aka an array.

data is a pointer

 
